          for terrestrial fibre; twin-field QKD (TF-QKD) breaks the repeaterless
          rate–loss bound by interfering single photons at a central station;
          satellite links use Micius-class downlinks to skip the fibre-loss
          budget entirely <SourceNote id="azuma-rmp-95" />.
        </p>

